text: Coon Creek is a stream in Faribault County, Minnesota and Kossuth County, Iowa. It is a tributary of the Blue Earth River. Coon Creek was named for the raccoons once hunted in the area for their fur. ==See also== *List of rivers of Iowa *List of rivers of Minnesota ==References== Category:Rivers of Faribault County, Minnesota Category:Bodies of water of Kossuth County, Iowa Category:Rivers of Iowa Category:Rivers of Minnesota
title: Coon Creek (Blue Earth River tributary)
